Apache2
-------
/etc/apache2/ports.conf should be modified to listen on 0.0.0.0:{port} to use IPv4.
Run 'a2enmod rewrite' to enable rewriting (which I use quite a bit).

Now including HTTPS, so we need 'a2enmod socach_shmcb' and 'a2enmdo ssl'.

Nice to have is 'a2enmod headers' and some faffing in the main apache2.conf.

Symlink to these files from /etc/apache2/sites-available (and those to sites-enabled):
fs-peter.conf
fs-peter-drealm-backup.conf
fs-peter-ssl.conf
jamuluswebsite.conf
steveholt.conf

README     - this file
htpasswd   - Used from inge/diet for Apache Basic Authentication (NOT in git)
tomcat.p12 - PKCS-12 keystore for SpringBoot applications (see 'tomcat.p12 keystore password') (NOT in git)
